  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "cell-039",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "**Observations — segmentation (Q2)**\n",
    "\n",
    "- **At Risk** (n=1,248): churn **70.0%** — 3.4× the 20.4% baseline; **Champion** (n=1,096): **5.4%** — lowest. The rules separate risk in the right direction and yield an actionable list with no model required.\n",
    "- Profile heatmap: At Risk = older, inactive, more products, highest Germany share (34.9%), higher female share (52.7%); Champion = long tenure + exactly 2 products + active — distinct enough for a per-segment retention playbook.\n",
    "- **Honest caveat on Promising**: churn 14.0% — NOT above baseline; `tenure` carries almost no signal (η² ≈ 0.0002). The \"new customers are highest-risk\" hypothesis is *not supported by this cross-sectional data* — keep Promising for onboarding purposes only.\n",
    "- *Hypothesis requiring an A/B test*: proactive outreach to At Risk reduces churn — currently correlation only.\n",
    "\n",
    "**Summary — EDA:** real data answers who/which-segment descriptively; trend-based claims rely on synthetic data (pipeline demo only). Carried into pre-processing: 20.37% imbalance, non-linear `age` (verified train-only in §4.4), the 5-feature set for Model B.\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "cell-040",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 4.4 Data pre-processing\n",
    "\n",
    "**Cleaning goal:** dedup + business-range validation (`age` 18–92, `balance ≥ 0`, `credit_score` 350–850), logging every dropped row.\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 23,
   "id": "cell-041",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "Cleaning log: {'rows_before': 10000, 'dupes_dropped': 0, 'invalid_flagged': 0, 'rows_after': 10000}\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "base_raw = pd.read_csv(\"../../data/raw/bank_customer_churn.csv\")\n",
    "log = {\"rows_before\": len(base_raw)}\n",
    "base_dedup = base_raw.drop_duplicates(\"customer_id\")\n",
    "log[\"dupes_dropped\"] = log[\"rows_before\"] - len(base_dedup)\n",
    "valid = (base_dedup[\"age\"].between(18, 92) & (base_dedup[\"balance\"] >= 0)\n",
    "         & base_dedup[\"credit_score\"].between(350, 850))\n",
    "log[\"invalid_flagged\"] = int((~valid).sum())\n",
    "base_clean = base_dedup[valid].copy()\n",
    "log[\"rows_after\"] = len(base_clean)\n",
    "base_clean.to_parquet(\"../../data/processed/base_clean_v3.parquet\", index=False)\n",
    "print(\"Cleaning log:\", log)\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "cell-042",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "**Observations:** 0 duplicates, 0 out-of-range rows — the raw file was already clean; cleaning is an audited safety net.\n",
    "\n",
    "**Canonical split ids.** Every preprocessing decision below (residual diagnostics, AIC, selection) must be fit on **train only**, so the split ids are created here — one split, keyed on `customer_id`, persisted to disk, reused by every downstream cell with assertions. The formal modeling split is rebuilt from this file in §5.1.\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 24,
   "id": "cell-043",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "train: 8000 | test: 2000\n",
      "churn rate — train: 0.2037 | test: 0.2035\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "from sklearn.model_selection import train_test_split\n",
    "\n",
    "train_ids, test_ids = train_test_split(base_clean[\"customer_id\"], test_size=0.2,\n",
    "                                       stratify=base_clean[\"churn\"], random_state=SEED)\n",
    "split_ids = {\"train_ids\": sorted(map(int, train_ids)), \"test_ids\": sorted(map(int, test_ids))}\n",
    "with open(\"../../data/processed/split_ids_v3.json\", \"w\") as f:\n",
    "    json.dump(split_ids, f)\n",
    "\n",
    "train_mask = base_clean[\"customer_id\"].isin(split_ids[\"train_ids\"])\n",
    "print(\"train:\", train_mask.sum(), \"| test:\", (~train_mask).sum())\n",
    "print(\"churn rate — train:\", round(base_clean.loc[train_mask, 'churn'].mean(), 4),\n",
    "      \"| test:\", round(base_clean.loc[~train_mask, 'churn'].mean(), 4))\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "cell-044",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### 4.4.1 Pearson residual diagnostics\n",
    "\n",
    "**Thesis.** The target is binary → an OLS `residplot` is the wrong diagnostic (two-band artifact). Use the **Pearson residual** from a logistic fit: `(y − p̂)/√(p̂(1−p̂))`; a non-flat LOWESS trend signals a missing non-linear term. Fit on the 8,000 **training rows only** so the feature-engineering decision is not contaminated by test information.\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 25,
   "id": "cell-045",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 1700x380 with 4 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    },
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "Pearson resid mean: -0.0129 | n = 8000 (train only)\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "import statsmodels.api as sm\n",
    "\n",
    "train_df = base_clean[train_mask].copy()\n",
    "diag_cols = [\"age\", \"balance\", \"credit_score\"]\n",
    "X_d = sm.add_constant(train_df[diag_cols]); y_d = train_df[\"churn\"]\n",
    "logit_base = sm.Logit(y_d, X_d).fit(disp=0)\n",
    "p_hat = logit_base.predict(X_d)\n",
    "resid = (y_d - p_hat) / np.sqrt(p_hat * (1 - p_hat))\n",
    "\n",
    "fig, axes = plt.subplots(1, 4, figsize=(17, 3.8))\n",
    "samp = train_df.sample(3000, random_state=SEED).index\n",
    "panels = [(p_hat.loc[samp], \"fitted probability\")] + [(train_df.loc[samp, c], c) for c in diag_cols]\n",
    "for ax, (x, name) in zip(axes, panels):\n",
    "    sns.regplot(x=x, y=resid.loc[samp], lowess=True, scatter_kws={\"alpha\": .12, \"s\": 8},\n",
    "                line_kws={\"color\": \"red\"}, ax=ax)\n",
    "    ax.axhline(0, color=\"black\", ls=\"--\"); ax.set_title(f\"Pearson resid vs {name}\")\n",
    "plt.tight_layout(); plt.savefig(f\"{FIG}/residual_diag_train_only_v3.png\", dpi=120); plt.show()\n",
    "print(\"Pearson resid mean:\", round(resid.mean(), 4), \"| n =\", len(train_df), \"(train only)\")\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "cell-046",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "**Observations:** the LOWESS trend bends clearly against `age` (flat for `balance`/`credit_score`) → a non-linear age term is missing from the linear specification. Remediation is compared next.\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "cell-047",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### 4.4.2 Binning, Upsampling\n",
    "\n",
    "**Binning question.** `age_band` (5 bins) vs. `age + age²` — which flattens the residual trend at lower AIC? Tie-break: stakeholder explainability. Train-only.\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 26,
   "id": "cell-048",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "AIC — linear age: 7387.4 | age_band: 7062.5 | age+age^2: 7081.9\n"
     ]
    },
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 1500x400 with 3 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "dfc = train_df.copy()\n",
    "dfc[\"age_band\"] = pd.cut(dfc[\"age\"], bins=[17, 29, 39, 49, 59, 100],\n",
    "                         labels=[\"18-29\", \"30-39\", \"40-49\", \"50-59\", \"60+\"])\n",
    "X_band = sm.add_constant(pd.concat([dfc[[\"balance\", \"credit_score\"]],\n",
    "        pd.get_dummies(dfc[\"age_band\"], prefix=\"age_band\", drop_first=True, dtype=int)], axis=1))\n",
    "m_band = sm.Logit(y_d, X_band).fit(disp=0)\n",
    "\n",
    "dfc[\"age_sq\"] = dfc[\"age\"] ** 2\n",
    "m_quad = sm.Logit(y_d, sm.add_constant(dfc[[\"age\", \"age_sq\", \"balance\", \"credit_score\"]])).fit(disp=0)\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f\"AIC — linear age: {logit_base.aic:.1f} | age_band: {m_band.aic:.1f} | age+age^2: {m_quad.aic:.1f}\")\n",
    "\n",
    "samp2 = dfc.sample(3000, random_state=SEED).index\n",
    "fig, axes = plt.subplots(1, 3, figsize=(15, 4), sharey=True)\n",
    "for ax, (m, X_m, title) in zip(axes, [(logit_base, X_d, \"Baseline: linear age\"),\n",
    "                                       (m_band, X_band, \"Option 1: age_band\"),\n",
    "                                       (m_quad, sm.add_constant(dfc[[\"age\", \"age_sq\", \"balance\", \"credit_score\"]]), \"Option 2: age + age^2\")]):\n",
    "    p = m.predict(X_m); r = (y_d - p) / np.sqrt(p * (1 - p))\n",
    "    sns.regplot(x=dfc.loc[samp2, \"age\"], y=r.loc[samp2], lowess=True, scatter_kws={\"alpha\": .12, \"s\": 8},\n",
    "                line_kws={\"color\": \"red\"}, ax=ax)\n",
    "    ax.axhline(0, color=\"black\", ls=\"--\"); ax.set_title(title)\n",
    "plt.tight_layout(); plt.savefig(f\"{FIG}/age_fix_comparison_v3.png\", dpi=120); plt.show()\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "cell-049",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "**Observations:** AIC — linear age 7387 → **age_band 7063** (winner) vs. age+age² 7082; both flatten the LOWESS trend. `age_band` wins on AIC and is easier to communicate (\"risk peaks at 50-59\") → **use `age_band`**, decided on training rows only.\n",
    "\n",
    "**Upsampling question.** Class imbalance (~1:4) — `class_weight=\"balanced\"` vs. **SMOTE** (synthetic minority oversampling): are they materially different on this data? 3-fold CV on train, real features only.\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 27,
   "id": "cell-050",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "class_weight='balanced'  AUC-ROC=0.7660  AUC-PR=0.4534\n",
      "SMOTE + LogReg           AUC-ROC=0.7650  AUC-PR=0.4518\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "from imblearn.over_sampling import SMOTE\n",
    "from imblearn.pipeline import Pipeline as ImbPipeline\n",
    "\n",
    "enc_cmp = pd.get_dummies(train_df.drop(columns=[\"customer_id\"]),\n",
    "                         columns=[\"country\", \"gender\"], drop_first=True, dtype=int)\n",
    "X_cmp = StandardScaler().fit_transform(enc_cmp.drop(columns=[\"churn\"]))\n",
    "y_cmp = enc_cmp[\"churn\"]\n",
    "cv3 = StratifiedKFold(3, shuffle=True, random_state=SEED)\n",
    "for name, est in [(\"class_weight='balanced'\", LogisticRegression(class_weight=\"balanced\", max_iter=500)),\n",
    "                  (\"SMOTE + LogReg\", ImbPipeline([(\"smote\", SMOTE(random_state=SEED)),\n",
    "                                                  (\"clf\", LogisticRegression(max_iter=500))]))]:\n",
    "    a = cross_val_score(est, X_cmp, y_cmp, cv=cv3, scoring=\"roc_auc\", n_jobs=-1)\n",
    "    p = cross_val_score(est, X_cmp, y_cmp, cv=cv3, scoring=\"average_precision\", n_jobs=-1)\n",
    "    print(f\"{name:24s} AUC-ROC={a.mean():.4f}  AUC-PR={p.mean():.4f}\")\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "cell-051",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "**Decision:** the two remedies are equivalent on this data (AUC-ROC 0.766 vs 0.766, AUC-PR 0.453 vs 0.452, 3-fold CV on real features). Model A (§5.2) adopts **SMOTE inside an imbalanced-learn `Pipeline`** because it composes cleanly with `SelectKBest` inside each CV fold (resampling and selection both leakage-safe); `class_weight=\"balanced\"` remains a documented fallback.\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "cell-052",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 4.5 Feature engineering & Encoding\n",
    "\n",
    "Merge behavioral aggregates + banking flags (`zero_balance`, `balance_to_salary_ratio`, `credit_score_tier`, `active_and_card`, `tenure_per_product`), replace `age` with `age_band` (§4.4.2), one-hot encode with `drop_first=True` (avoids the dummy trap upfront); **keep `customer_id`** so every downstream cell aligns the split by id.\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 28,
   "id": "cell-053",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "features_v3: (10000, 32) | missing: 0\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "feat = base_clean.merge(open_dates, on=\"customer_id\").merge(agg, on=\"customer_id\")\n",
    "feat[\"zero_balance\"] = (feat[\"balance\"] == 0).astype(int)\n",
    "feat[\"balance_to_salary_ratio\"] = (feat[\"balance\"] / feat[\"estimated_salary\"].replace(0, np.nan)).fillna(0)\n",
    "feat[\"age_band\"] = pd.cut(feat[\"age\"], bins=[17, 29, 39, 49, 59, 100],\n",
    "                          labels=[\"18-29\", \"30-39\", \"40-49\", \"50-59\", \"60+\"])\n",
    "feat[\"credit_score_tier\"] = pd.cut(feat[\"credit_score\"], bins=[0, 580, 670, 740, 800, 850],\n",
    "                                   labels=[\"poor\", \"fair\", \"good\", \"very_good\", \"excellent\"])\n",
    "feat[\"active_and_card\"] = (feat[\"active_member\"] * feat[\"credit_card\"]).astype(int)\n",
    "feat[\"tenure_per_product\"] = (feat[\"tenure\"] / feat[\"products_number\"].replace(0, np.nan)).fillna(0)\n",
    "\n",
    "feat_encoded = pd.get_dummies(feat, columns=[\"country\", \"gender\", \"age_band\", \"credit_score_tier\"],\n",
    "                              drop_first=True, dtype=int)\n",
    "feat_encoded = feat_encoded.drop(columns=[\"account_open_date\", \"last_active_month\", \"age\", \"credit_score\"])\n",
    "assert feat_encoded.drop(columns=[\"churn\", \"customer_id\"]).select_dtypes(exclude=[np.number, \"bool\"]).empty\n",
    "feat_encoded.to_parquet(\"../../data/processed/features_v3.parquet\", index=False)\n",
    "print(\"features_v3:\", feat_encoded.shape, \"| missing:\", feat_encoded.isna().sum().sum())\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "cell-054",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "**Summary — Data preparation:** canonical split keyed on `customer_id`; diagnostics/AIC/imbalance comparison all train-only → leakage-safe end to end; `age_band` replaces raw `age` (AIC-validated); feature table saved with `customer_id` for downstream alignment.\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "cell-055",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
